full_plan: A comprehensive real estate analytics dashboard showcasing: 1) Key market metrics with KPI cards, 2) Price distribution by property type and neighborhood, 3) Temporal trends and seasonality, 4) Feature impact analysis, 5) Geographic insights, 6) Property characteristics, 7) Market velocity metrics.

charts.title: Average Price by Property Type
charts.subtitle: Comparing median prices across different property types
charts.plan: Create a bar chart showing average prices by property type to identify the most expensive property categories
charts.chart_spec:
# Calculate average price by property type
price_by_type = df.groupby('property_type')['price'].agg(['mean', 'median', 'count']).reset_index()
price_by_type = price_by_type.sort_values('median', ascending=False)

# Create bar chart
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(
    x=price_by_type['property_type'],
    y=price_by_type['median'],
    name='Median Price',
    marker_color='#FF6B6B',
    text=price_by_type['median'].apply(lambda x: f'${x:,.0f}'),
    textposition='outside'
))
fig.update_layout(
    title='Average Price by Property Type',
    xaxis_title='Property Type',
    yaxis_title='Median Price ($)',
    showlegend=False,
    height=500
)

charts.title: Price Distribution by Neighborhood
charts.subtitle: Box plot showing price ranges across neighborhoods
charts.plan: Create a box plot to visualize price distributions and identify premium neighborhoods
charts.chart_spec:
# Get top 10 neighborhoods by median price
top_neighborhoods = df.groupby('neighborhood')['price'].median().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10).index
df_top = df[df['neighborhood'].isin(top_neighborhoods)]

# Create box plot
fig = px.box(df_top, x='neighborhood', y='price', 
             title='Price Distribution in Top 10 Neighborhoods',
             color='neighborhood',
             labels={'price': 'Price ($)', 'neighborhood': 'Neighborhood'})
fig.update_layout(showlegend=False, height=500)
fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=-45)

charts.title: Quarterly Price Trends
charts.subtitle: Time series showing price evolution over quarters
charts.plan: Create a line chart showing price trends over time by quarter
charts.chart_spec:
# Calculate quarterly average prices
quarterly_prices = df.groupby('sale_quarter')['price'].mean().reset_index()

# Create line chart
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
    x=quarterly_prices['sale_quarter'],
    y=quarterly_prices['price'],
    mode='lines+markers',
    line=dict(color='#FF6B6B', width=3),
    marker=dict(size=8),
    name='Average Price'
))
fig.update_layout(
    title='Quarterly Price Trends',
    xaxis_title='Quarter',
    yaxis_title='Average Price ($)',
    showlegend=False,
    height=500
)

charts.title: Property Size vs. Price
charts.subtitle: Scatter plot showing correlation between living area and price
charts.plan: Create a scatter plot to analyze the relationship between property size and price
charts.chart_spec:
# Create scatter plot with property type color coding
fig = px.scatter(df, x='sqft_living', y='price', 
                 color='property_type',
                 title='Property Size vs. Price',
                 labels={'sqft_living': 'Living Area (sqft)', 'price': 'Price ($)'},
                 opacity=0.6,
                 trendline='ols')
fig.update_layout(height=500)

charts.title: Waterfront Property Premium
charts.subtitle: Comparing prices for waterfront vs non-waterfront properties
charts.plan: Create a violin plot to show price distribution difference between waterfront and non-waterfront properties
charts.chart_spec:
# Create violin plot
fig = px.violin(df, x='waterfront', y='price',
                title='Waterfront Property Premium',
                labels={'waterfront': 'Waterfront Property', 'price': 'Price ($)'},
                color='waterfront',
                box=True)
fig.update_layout(height=500, showlegend=False)
fig.update_xaxes(ticktext=['Non-Waterfront', 'Waterfront'], tickvals=[0, 1])

charts.title: Impact of School Ratings on Price
charts.subtitle: Bar chart showing average prices by school rating
charts.plan: Analyze how school ratings affect property prices
charts.chart_spec:
# Calculate average price by school rating
price_by_school = df.groupby('school_rating')['price'].mean().reset_index()

# Create bar chart
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(
    x=price_by_school['school_rating'],
    y=price_by_school['price'],
    marker_color='#FF6B6B',
    text=price_by_school['price'].apply(lambda x: f'${x:,.0f}'),
    textposition='outside'
))
fig.update_layout(
    title='Impact of School Ratings on Price',
    xaxis_title='School Rating',
    yaxis_title='Average Price ($)',
    showlegend=False,
    height=500
)

title.text: Impact of School Ratings on Price

charts.title: Market Share by Price Segment
charts.subtitle: Pie chart showing distribution of properties across price segments
charts.plan: Create a pie chart to show market composition by price segment
charts.chart_spec:
# Calculate market share by price segment
segment_counts = df['price_segment'].value_counts()

# Create pie chart
fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Pie(
    labels=segment_counts.index,
    values=segment_counts.values,
    hole=0.4,
    marker_colors=['#FF6B6B', '#4ECDC4', '#45B7D1', '#FFA07A']
)])
fig.update_layout(
    title='Market Share by Price Segment',
    height=500
)

charts.title: Days on Market by Price Segment
charts.subtitle: Box plot showing market velocity across price segments
charts.plan: Analyze how quickly properties sell in different price segments
charts.chart_spec:
# Create box plot
fig = px.box(df, x='price_segment', y='days_on_market',
             title='Days on Market by Price Segment',
             labels={'price_segment': 'Price Segment', 'days_on_market': 'Days on Market'},
             color='price_segment')
fig.update_layout(height=500, showlegend=False)

title.text: Days on Market by Price Segment

charts.title: Property Features Heatmap
charts.subtitle: Correlation matrix of key property features
charts.plan: Create a heatmap to show correlations between different property features
charts.chart_spec:
# Select numeric columns for correlation
numeric_cols = ['price', 'sqft_living', 'bedrooms', 'bathrooms', 'floors', 
                'waterfront', 'view_quality', 'condition', 'grade', 'school_rating']
corr_matrix = df[numeric_cols].corr()

# Create heatmap
fig = go.Figure(data=go.Heatmap(
    z=corr_matrix.values,
    x=corr_matrix.columns,
    y=corr_matrix.columns,
    colorscale='RdBu',
    zmid=0,
    text=corr_matrix.values.round(2),
    texttemplate='%{text}',
    textfont={"size": 10}
))
fig.update_layout(
    title='Property Features Correlation Heatmap',
    height=600,
    width=700
)

charts.title: Property Age vs. Price
charts.subtitle: Scatter plot showing relationship between property age and price
charts.plan: Analyze how property age affects pricing
charts.chart_spec:
# Create renovation status column
df['renovation_status'] = df['year_renovated'].apply(lambda x: 'Renovated' if x > 0 else 'Original')

# Create scatter plot
fig = px.scatter(df, x='property_age', y='price',
                 color='renovation_status',
                 title='Property Age vs. Price',
                 labels={'property_age': 'Property Age (years)', 'price': 'Price ($)'},
                 opacity=0.6)
fig.update_layout(height=500)
